Modelling the buying behaviour of customers – retaining customers is cheaper than getting new customers


Understanding churn behaviour in customers – especially in the highly competitive Omni channel market

Understanding customers segments and how they behave differently – mass marketing does not work for everyone


#############

Collect and analyse customer data and bring out clusters based on demographics and buying behaviour

Model customer churn behaviour after first purchase to make her a repeat buyer, using survival analysis

Prescriptive models help devise the best promotions that will affect the customer’s buying behaviour at the right time

#################
Personalized marketing campaigns reduces costs and improves customer satisfaction

Timely intervention with promotions reduces churn and promotes customer loyalty
